a more realistic physics system and propose \u003Cem\u003Emovable celestial bodies\u003C/em\u003E as a positive?\u003Cbr\u003E\nNot a better aerodynamic model, not kraken extermination, but movable planets?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you think Unity is right now? Unreal Engine 16? It may be a physics sandbox, but it\u0027s not \u003Ca href=\u0022https://universesandbox.com/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EUniverse Sandbox.\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Go play that instead if you\u0027d really want entire\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eplanets\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0to be moved somehow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T15:54:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113288\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649432539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you think Unity is right now? Unreal Engine 16?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree with everything else, but here you imply that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Unity is bad, or at least worse than Unreal (which it isn\u0027t)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. That having planets move and influence each other gravitationally would be difficult. This has already been modded into KSP 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Catto","CreatedById":137773,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:26:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah it should i guess\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:28:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113302\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649433292\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree with everything else, but here you imply that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Unity is bad, or at least worse than Unreal (which it isn\u0027t)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. That having planets move and influence each other gravitationally would be difficult. This has already been modded into KSP 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. I didn\u0027t mean to imply that, Unity\u0027s great, but I have this idea that \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E thinks of realistic as being \u0022cool\u0022 like Unreal Engine\u0027s uber-realistic graphics nowadays, instead of \u0022cool\u0022 like \u0022oh hey I can actually make an aircraft that functions as it would in reality\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. But the actual tidal forces of such an event would have to be completely ignored in order to function on the computers of today. Hardly \u0022realistic\u0022, is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:28:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435197\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137773\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022siklidkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, siklidkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah it should i guess\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435288\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. But the actual tidal forces of such an event would have to be completely ignored in order to function on the computers of today. Hardly \u0022realistic\u0022, is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis isn\u0027t needed anyway\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Catto","CreatedById":137773,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:29:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me put it in more detail: KSP2 should have a better phys engine than KSP1, but not by that much. The developers still want newbies to the game to learn about it well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137773\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022siklidkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, siklidkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me put it in more detail: KSP2 should have a better phys engine than KSP1, but not by that much. The developers still want newbies to the game to learn about it well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea what i\u0027m saying, i\u0027m not an astrophysicist.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:30:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137773\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022siklidkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, siklidkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me put it in more detail: KSP2 should have a better phys engine than KSP1, but not by that much. The developers still want newbies to the game to learn about it well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRealistic =/= difficult. People seem to think \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E is more difficult than the stock game, but that\u0027s far from reality. The idea that realism makes things difficult only goes so far.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Catto","CreatedById":137773,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:32:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113343\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435433\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRealistic =/= difficult. People seem to think \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is more difficult than the stock game, but that\u0027s far from reality. The idea that realism makes things difficult only goes so far.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah. It\u0027s not going to be that realistic, but atleast a little more realistic, with all the new parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:36:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis isn\u0027t needed anyway\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe moon causes significant tides, and you\u0027re telling me that if an Earth-sized planet were to pass closer to Earth than the moon is, just barely skimming the atmosphere, that tidal forces don\u0027t mean anything in that situation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:41:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113349\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435815\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis isn\u0027t needed anyway\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe moon causes significant tides, and you\u0027re telling me that if an Earth-sized planet were to pass closer to Earth than the moon is, just barely skimming the atmosphere, that tidal forces don\u0027t mean anything in that situation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEt cetera et cetera, whatever. Temperature and roche spheres can be static values, it doesn\u0027t matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:49:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113352\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649436097\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEt cetera et cetera, whatever. Temperature and roche spheres can be static values, it doesn\u0027t matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEither:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou ignore the effects of such a close pass, so it\u0027s no longer \u0022realistic\u0022, as is the point of this post, or;\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou include the effects of such a close pass, so your computer reaches the heat of a nuclear reactor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust leave the planets on rails, moving them isn\u0027t important or within KSP2\u0027s idea of \u0022rational situations\u0022. Stop insisting the planets need to move.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-08T16:49:29Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2022 04:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by intelliCom\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T16:51:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113363\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649436553\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou ignore the effects of such a close pass, so it\u0027s no longer \u0022realistic\u0022, as is the point of this post, or;\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou include the effects of such a close pass, so your computer reaches the heat of a nuclear reactor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRask and Rusk should be evidence enough you don\u0027t have to simulate tidal effects to just model the effects in a static manner.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113363\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649436553\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust leave the planets on rails, moving them isn\u0027t important or within KSP2\u0027s idea of \u0022rational situations\u0022. Stop insisting the planets need to move.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLiterally my first message to you here was me agreeing that the planets don\u0027t need to move. You don\u0027t like it when I misquote you, so why are you misrepresenting me? Everything on from that point was me just going along for the sake of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113349\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649435815\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe moon causes significant tides, and you\u0027re telling me that if an Earth-sized planet were to pass closer to Earth than the moon is, just barely skimming the atmosphere, that tidal forces don\u0027t mean anything in that situation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy are you insisting that the planets need to move and have simulated tidal effects?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T17:05:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649436705\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLiterally my first message to you here was me agreeing that the planets don\u0027t need to move. You don\u0027t like it when I misquote you, so why are you misrepresenting me? Everything on from that point was me just going along for the sake of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause I was trying to explain how even\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eattempting\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0to try and make moving planets \u0022realistic\u0022 would run into so many problems that suddenly make it less realistic all over again. I\u0027m trying to stay with the post\u0027s topic here. Yes, there\u0027s mods for it. Yes, \u0022moving planets\u0022 can work. But \u0022moving planets\u0022 suddenly introduces a bunch of extra issues in realism that make it not worth it to begin with, as per \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s motivation for a more realistic physics engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EThis\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0is why I compared such a feat to \u0022Unreal Engine 15\u0022. Because trying to make such physics \u0022realistic\u0022 would put such an unbelievable amount of strain on a computer that it\u0027s not even practical for a scientific simulation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not processing moving planets\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eon its own\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0that\u0027s intensive. It\u0027s making \u003Cem\u003Ethat\u003C/em\u003E \u0022realistic.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113302\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649433292\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat having planets move and influence each other gravitationally would be difficult. This has already been modded into KSP 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-08T17:05:35Z\u0022 title=\u002204/08/2022 05:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 8, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by intelliCom\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"snkiz","CreatedById":176192,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T18:54:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really a yes or no question when you think about it. How high should they make the minimum spec? What activities do you prioritize? Is it even the physics engines fault?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe fist one is obvious, were it all proper N-body It would very quickly replace the crisis meme, not in a good way. So you will have to compromise. Some things might be difficult to make behave correctly across all possible flight regimes. Going from water, to\u00A0 air to vacuum. And Then is the physics even your problem? \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t really change the game physics, just how it presents your craft as a unified body, as opposed to the stock collection parts flying in linked formation with arcane oclusion rules and drag cubes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I will say is I wish the physics were more intuitive in the way it handles the overall shape of crafts. A way to \u0027weld\u0027 joints that would have been\u00A0 IRL, like fuselage parts in line. Some fake N-body, specifically Lagrange points. They are talked about often when discussing IRL missions. So some simple representation of them, but still on rails would be good enough IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-08T19:56:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113379\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649437525\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224113365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022207632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649436705\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLiterally my first message to you here was me agreeing that the planets don\u0027t need to move. You don\u0027t like it when I misquote you, so why are you misrepresenting me? Everything on from that point was me just going along for the sake of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause I was trying to explain how even\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eattempting\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0to try and make mov\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I was only going along.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maria Sirona","CreatedById":210882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-16T12:27:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRealistic enough already.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}